parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front End Alignment and Suspension Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the front end and suspension problems can cause uneven tire wear, vibrations, and noise, leading to reduced vehicle stability and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of U-bolts can cause the axle to shift, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of front wheel bearings can cause vibrations, noise, and uneven tire wear, leading to reduced vehicle stability and increased risk of accidents.
The malfunction of the air ride system can cause the vehicle to lean to one side, leading to reduced vehicle stability and increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wiring Harness Failure under the Dash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness under the dash can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to issues with the dashboard instruments, lighting, and other essential systems, which can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
The failure of the starter can cause the vehicle to be unable to start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially causing safety issues in certain situations.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to start
the starter motor fails to engage
the starter motor makes unusual noises or smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Eaton 13-speed transmission can cause the vehicle to experience problems with shifting, overheating, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: bucking or jerking of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to experience difficulties with shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Axle Overweight and Premature Tire Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overweight axle can cause premature wear of tires, leading to loss of traction, accidents, and reduced vehicle safety.
symptoms: Extreme vibration in the front end of the vehicle
